text: Chemaudin et Vaux is a commune. It is in Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in the Doubs department in east France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2017 and consists of the former communes of Chemaudin (the seat) and Vaux-les- Prés.Arrêté préfectoral 12 August 2016 == References == Category:2017 establishments in France Category:Communes in Doubs
title: Chemaudin et Vaux
